---
import RedSectionHeader from "../common/RedSectionHeader.astro";
---

<section class="py-20 bg-white" id="withdrawal-guide">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <RedSectionHeader
            title="Exit Strategy: Withdrawal & Early Access"
            className="mb-12"
        />

        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-700 max-w-none">
            <p class="mb-12 text-xl leading-relaxed">
                The golden rule of Pillar 3a is that it is "Gebunden" (Locked).
                However, Switzerland recognizes that life happens. There are
                five specific keys that unlock this box before retirement age.
            </p>

            <!-- 10.2 Early Withdrawal Scenarios -->
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-16">
                <div
                    class="bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-red-600"
                >
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        1. Financing a Home (WEF)
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-sm mb-4">
                        You can withdraw capital to buy a primary residence (not
                        a holiday home or rental).
                    </p>
                    <ul class="text-sm list-disc pl-5">
                        <li><strong>Minimum:</strong> CHF 20,000 (usually).</li>
                        <li><strong>Frequency:</strong> Once every 5 years.</li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Tax:</strong> Immediate capital tax is triggered.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Alternative:</strong> "Pledging" (Verpf√§ndung)
                            to higher LTV without triggering tax.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-blue-600"
                >
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        2. Leaving Switzerland
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-sm mb-4">
                        The expat wildcard. If you leave Switzerland
                        permanently:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="text-sm list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Non-EU/EFTA:</strong> Cash out 100% of the capital.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>EU/EFTA:</strong> Cash out 100% of the 3a capital
                            (restrictions apply mostly to 2nd pillar).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Timing:</strong> Do this <em>after</em> deregistration
                            to potentially pay Withholding Tax at the canton of the
                            foundation (e.g. Schwyz) rather than your domicile.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-yellow-500"
                >
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        3. Self-Employment
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-sm mb-4">Becoming your own boss?</p>
                    <ul class="text-sm list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>
                            You can withdraw capital to finance your startup.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Must be done within 1 year of starting the business.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Requires proof of "Self-Employed Status" to the
                            compensation office (SVA).
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-gray-500"
                >
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        4. Disability / Death
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-sm mb-4">
                        In tragic circumstances, the funds are released.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="text-sm list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>Full IV (Disability) pension triggered.</li>
                        <li>
                            Death: Capital goes to beneficiaries (Spouse > Kids
                            > Others). 3a falls into preferential inheritance
                            law.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 10.3 Withdrawal Tax Rates -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    The "Pain" of Withdrawal: Taxes
                </h3>
                <p>
                    When you withdraw, you pay a separate Capital Tax. It is
                    progressive (the more you take, the higher the %), but much
                    lower than income tax.
                </p>

                <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
                    <table
                        class="min-w-full text-sm border-collapse border border-gray-200"
                    >
                        <thead>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                                <th class="p-3 text-left border">Canton</th>
                                <th class="p-3 text-left border"
                                    >Approx. Tax on CHF 100k</th
                                >
                                <th class="p-3 text-left border"
                                    >Approx. Tax on CHF 500k</th
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
                            <tr
                                ><td class="p-3">Zurich</td><td class="p-3"
                                    >~5.2%</td
                                ><td class="p-3">~7.8%</td></tr
                            >
                            <tr
                                ><td class="p-3">Geneva</td><td class="p-3"
                                    >~6.8%</td
                                ><td class="p-3">~10.5%</td></tr
                            >
                            <tr
                                ><td class="p-3">Vaud</td><td class="p-3"
                                    >~7.1%</td
                                ><td class="p-3">~11.2%</td></tr
                            >
                            <tr
                                ><td class="p-3 font-bold text-green-700"
                                    >Zug (Low Tax)</td
                                ><td class="p-3 text-green-700">~2.5%</td><td
                                    class="p-3 text-green-700">~5.1%</td
                                ></tr
                            >
                            <tr
                                ><td class="p-3 font-bold text-green-700"
                                    >Schwyz (Low Tax)</td
                                ><td class="p-3 text-green-700">~2.8%</td><td
                                    class="p-3 text-green-700">~5.4%</td
                                ></tr
                            >
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">
                        *Indicative figures only. Rates change annually and
                        depend on municipal multipliers. Consult a tax advisor.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 10.1 Steps -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    The Payout Process
                </h3>
                <ol class="relative border-l border-gray-200 ml-4 space-y-8">
                    <li class="mb-10 ml-4">
                        <div
                            class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-red-600 rounded-full mt-1.5 -left-1.5 border border-white"
                        >
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
                            Step 1: Initiate (Age 60-65)
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                            Contact provider 3 months before desired payout.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-10 ml-4">
                        <div
                            class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-red-600 rounded-full mt-1.5 -left-1.5 border border-white"
                        >
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
                            Step 2: Signatures
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                            Spousal consent is mandatory for 3a withdrawals
                            (they must sign too).
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-10 ml-4">
                        <div
                            class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-red-600 rounded-full mt-1.5 -left-1.5 border border-white"
                        >
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
                            Step 3: Transfer & Tax
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                            Gross Money hits your account. Within 30-90 days,
                            you receive a separate tax bill from the canton.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
